WEBVTT

00:01.042 --> 00:03.170
[♪ opening theme song playing]

01:35.262 --> 01:38.640
[REGGIE] Believe me,
the rules' idea of continuation

01:38.682 --> 01:41.769
is nothing but a cover
for the real plan.

01:41.810 --> 01:43.311
Mark my words.

01:43.353 --> 01:45.146
When only the strong remain,

01:45.188 --> 01:48.316
Kenjaku is going to drop
a bomb on the game.

01:48.358 --> 01:51.653
And the Culling Game
will fulfill its real purpose.

01:51.695 --> 01:54.823
I don't know what kind of bomb
Kenjaku's going to drop,

01:55.365 --> 01:57.743
but it's going to happen
in the near future,

01:57.785 --> 01:59.036
that's for sure.

01:59.536 --> 02:01.204
Maybe even this very moment.

02:01.663 --> 02:05.459
That's why I'm preparing
by gathering strong allies

02:05.500 --> 02:07.419
and stocking up points.

02:07.920 --> 02:09.588
I have a few questions.

02:10.839 --> 02:13.341
Is she strong enough?
Because I have my doubts.

02:13.383 --> 02:14.885
It doesn't matter
if she's strong

02:14.927 --> 02:16.261
because I'm just
using her as bait

02:16.303 --> 02:18.013
to attract other players here.

02:18.472 --> 02:21.224
People tend to be less wary
of women, you know.

02:22.141 --> 02:23.351
So when you're done using her,

02:23.393 --> 02:25.228
you'll just kill her
for the points?

02:27.230 --> 02:29.399
I don't know
what you're talking about.

02:29.441 --> 02:31.026
I'd never do that.

02:31.693 --> 02:34.613
Even though you're a bust,
Reggie's my actual true knight!

02:34.989 --> 02:36.239
As long as I serve him,

02:36.281 --> 02:37.992
he'll protect me
from all danger!

02:38.533 --> 02:40.159
How naive and stupid.

02:40.828 --> 02:42.287
Do you and your allies possess

02:42.329 --> 02:44.331
at least 100 points
between all of you?

02:44.873 --> 02:47.042
[scoffs] Most certainly.

02:47.584 --> 02:49.461
[MEGUMI]
A new rule will be added soon.

02:50.211 --> 02:53.172
It'll allow players to transfer
points between each other.

02:54.758 --> 02:56.551
- Hand over your points.
- [growls]

02:56.593 --> 02:58.177
I need them for myself.

02:58.219 --> 03:00.806
Seems like negotiations
have broken down.

03:00.848 --> 03:02.016
[door creaks, slams]

03:02.057 --> 03:03.642
[whooshing]

03:06.020 --> 03:07.312
- [REGGIE] He's...
- [CHIZURU]...gone.

03:07.604 --> 03:08.939
[grunting]

03:09.606 --> 03:10.649
[CHIZARU] Hey!

03:11.358 --> 03:12.526
Nue!

03:12.567 --> 03:13.652
[Reggie gasps]

03:14.862 --> 03:15.904
[MEGUMI] Hey.

03:16.697 --> 03:18.365
Don't let me
see your face again.

03:18.406 --> 03:20.784
- [gasps]
- [Demon Dog whines]

03:21.660 --> 03:23.202
[REGGIE] Ah.

03:23.871 --> 03:26.498
- [groans]
- [REGGIE] I get it, I get it.

03:26.832 --> 03:28.542
I thought you were holding back,

03:28.583 --> 03:31.003
but you can't kill us, can you?

03:31.045 --> 03:33.922
You want our points,
but only if we give them to you.

03:34.213 --> 03:35.423
But I think

03:35.757 --> 03:37.885
if you fight
without trying to kill,

03:38.385 --> 03:41.304
you'll regret it the moment
you realize you're dead.

03:47.061 --> 03:48.062
[gasps]

04:00.824 --> 04:02.283
[loud crash]

04:05.328 --> 04:06.329
[REGGIE] Hey!

04:06.621 --> 04:08.165
I'm down here, too, you know!

04:09.332 --> 04:10.417
He dead yet?

04:11.126 --> 04:12.169
[coughs]

04:13.336 --> 04:14.421
[whooshing]

04:16.339 --> 04:17.424
[groans]

04:19.093 --> 04:20.301
You good with this?

04:23.180 --> 04:24.263
This smell.

04:38.862 --> 04:39.905
Is it over?

04:40.864 --> 04:42.574
[IORI] Not yet.

04:42.616 --> 04:43.658
Just like you.

04:44.243 --> 04:46.954
He ran into a room
before the explosion hit.

04:47.412 --> 04:49.706
Huh. Not bad at all.

04:50.331 --> 04:53.043
Good work.
I bet you wore him down a lot.

04:54.669 --> 04:56.171
[creaking, clanging]

04:56.213 --> 04:58.465
[groaning softly]

05:00.926 --> 05:02.261
[MEGUMI] Do you finally get it?

05:03.053 --> 05:05.139
They have no intention
of protecting you.

05:05.180 --> 05:07.348
[Remi groaning]

05:07.390 --> 05:08.558
[groans softly]

05:08.600 --> 05:09.684
Now you know.

05:10.060 --> 05:11.519
So get outta here.

05:13.021 --> 05:14.148
- [thuds]
- [exclaims]

05:19.236 --> 05:20.904
Give it a rest already.

05:21.613 --> 05:22.781
[REMI] Then,

05:23.198 --> 05:24.365
say it.

05:26.034 --> 05:28.578
Reggie said it
when I asked him to!

05:28.620 --> 05:30.329
He said he'd protect me!

05:30.371 --> 05:32.874
He said he liked me!

05:32.916 --> 05:34.751
So you say it!

05:37.212 --> 05:38.463
Ugh.

05:40.381 --> 05:41.842
I've seen them all.

05:42.717 --> 05:44.511
Scumbags like you

05:45.053 --> 05:47.889
who care more about words
than real action.

05:48.431 --> 05:50.349
[CHIZURU]
That was a heck of a throw!

05:51.018 --> 05:52.853
But now you're all banged up.

05:53.270 --> 05:55.022
Wasn't easy
climbing back up here,

05:55.063 --> 05:56.106
but I made it.

05:57.107 --> 05:59.026
[MEGUMI] Use the stairs
next time, Neanderthal.

05:59.067 --> 06:02.154
[KOGANE] Ding-dong, ding-dong,
ding-dong, ding-dong, ding-dong!

06:02.196 --> 06:04.405
Your attention please,
your attention.

06:04.447 --> 06:07.450
A player has added a new rule
to the Culling Game.

06:08.409 --> 06:09.786
Rule Number Ten.

06:09.828 --> 06:11.288
Players are able to transfer

06:11.330 --> 06:13.207
a number of points
of their choosing

06:13.248 --> 06:14.666
to other players in the game.

06:15.042 --> 06:16.918
[CHIZURU]
What kind of rule is that?

06:18.879 --> 06:20.172
[grunts]

06:25.468 --> 06:26.511
[sword clatters]

06:28.222 --> 06:29.348
[grunts]

06:32.600 --> 06:33.643
[croaks]

06:35.187 --> 06:36.188
[grunts, gasps]

06:36.521 --> 06:38.315
[struggling grunts]

06:38.606 --> 06:39.816
[straining]

06:41.902 --> 06:43.611
[groaning]

06:44.321 --> 06:46.531
[groaning]

06:48.491 --> 06:49.701
[grunts]

06:50.744 --> 06:51.995
[MEGUMI] Max Elephant!

06:52.037 --> 06:53.121
[gasps]

06:53.621 --> 06:54.664
[elephant trumpets]

06:54.706 --> 06:55.957
[CHIZURU] He did it again!

06:57.042 --> 06:58.626
[Nue screeches]

07:00.212 --> 07:01.255
[grunts]

07:02.421 --> 07:03.590
[groans]

07:04.132 --> 07:05.550
- [loud crash]
- [bicycle bell rings]

07:08.845 --> 07:10.555
[grunting]

07:10.597 --> 07:12.974
You bastard! How dare you?

07:13.683 --> 07:14.935
- [stabs]
- [groans]

07:14.976 --> 07:16.103
[blood splatters]

07:19.106 --> 07:20.523
[MEGUMI] What am I doing?

07:22.650 --> 07:25.070
I'll need more points
in the future,

07:25.112 --> 07:27.281
but Tsumiki won't be forced
to participate

07:27.322 --> 07:28.907
in the killing anymore.

07:29.532 --> 07:30.825
Just be patient.

07:30.867 --> 07:32.493
Believe in the others.

07:32.535 --> 07:34.495
Don't obsess
over these guys' points.

07:35.289 --> 07:37.416
All I need to do
is use my full might

07:37.456 --> 07:40.085
to brush away any sparks
that might fall on me.

07:40.543 --> 07:42.921
You have gained five points
for a kill.

07:43.755 --> 07:46.465
[REGGIE] Man,
what a waste of points.

07:47.092 --> 07:48.676
How pathetic, getting killed

07:48.718 --> 07:50.637
before he could
even use his technique.

07:52.722 --> 07:54.433
[MEGUMI] Did Remi drop out?

07:54.849 --> 07:56.726
Even so, it's still two on one.

07:57.518 --> 08:00.063
Damn it, I'm still reeling
from that first explosion.

08:00.814 --> 08:02.983
But fleeing ' s not an option.

08:03.942 --> 08:05.610
Maybe I should use my domain.

08:06.361 --> 08:07.988
No, bad idea.

08:08.029 --> 08:09.406
It's still incomplete.

08:09.781 --> 08:11.199
There's no way
I can close the barrier

08:11.241 --> 08:12.533
and trap them inside.

08:13.327 --> 08:15.078
The worst outcome

08:15.120 --> 08:17.538
would be them running off
and making me waste it.

08:17.580 --> 08:19.040
[whooshing]

08:21.126 --> 08:23.420
- [TAKABA] Look out!
- [explosion]

08:23.795 --> 08:25.339
- ...out!
- [explosion]

08:25.380 --> 08:26.923
- ...out!
- [explosion]

08:26.965 --> 08:28.591
- ...out!
- [explosion]

08:32.637 --> 08:34.306
Two on one, huh?

08:35.390 --> 08:36.557
I guess in your books,

08:36.599 --> 08:38.726
that's what you consider
a fair fight?

08:39.353 --> 08:41.104
Well, not in mine.

08:41.980 --> 08:43.231
Where I'm from,

08:43.273 --> 08:46.151
do you know what
they call people like you?

08:46.193 --> 08:48.736
They call them cowards!

08:49.196 --> 08:52.032
And cowardly attacks
won't work on me!

08:52.824 --> 08:54.201
Behold!

08:55.494 --> 08:59.373
Zero damage!

09:03.168 --> 09:04.543
[Megumi groans]

09:04.585 --> 09:05.962
[sighs]

09:07.881 --> 09:10.175
[sighs, groans]

09:26.233 --> 09:27.608
[groans]

09:27.650 --> 09:29.819
[exhales]

09:37.369 --> 09:39.954
[sighs]

09:47.003 --> 09:49.214
Young boy, I can help you!

09:49.256 --> 09:51.007
I turned 35 this year.

09:51.049 --> 09:52.551
With one look at someone's face,

09:52.591 --> 09:54.928
I can tell if they're
a good or bad person.

09:57.514 --> 09:58.723
What's wrong?

09:58.890 --> 10:02.310
Yucks! Anyone ever tell you
you got one bad face?

10:02.352 --> 10:03.478
[Megumi grumbles]

10:03.770 --> 10:04.729
Oh, well!

10:04.771 --> 10:06.314
I use a relative scale,

10:06.356 --> 10:07.482
just like schools!

10:07.524 --> 10:09.150
Schools use absolute scales.

10:09.776 --> 10:11.694
- He did protect me.
- [Takaba sniffs]

10:11.736 --> 10:13.905
So I guess
I can trust him for now.

10:14.781 --> 10:16.074
Well, Hazenoki,

10:16.116 --> 10:17.284
what do you make of him?

10:17.325 --> 10:18.535
I don't know the guy.

10:18.577 --> 10:20.203
It's quicker just to ask him.

10:20.454 --> 10:21.829
- Hey!
- [TAKABA] Hmm?

10:21.871 --> 10:23.790
Type. Which are you?

10:26.625 --> 10:28.503
[grunts] Mm.

10:29.254 --> 10:30.547
I get it now.

10:30.589 --> 10:32.840
You're asking what type
of comedian I am.

10:33.550 --> 10:34.926
The type that's always funny?

10:35.260 --> 10:37.095
Or the ones
deluding themselves?

10:37.137 --> 10:38.763
That's what
you're asking, right?

10:39.680 --> 10:41.933
[IORA] No, I'm asking what era--

10:42.225 --> 10:45.186
This costume is modeled
after my hero.

10:45.228 --> 10:47.439
The person who first
made me laugh my guts out

10:47.481 --> 10:48.731
when I was a child!

10:49.899 --> 10:51.734
So to honor this costume,

10:52.068 --> 10:54.321
I cannot allow my jokes
to fall flat!

10:54.529 --> 10:56.990
Here's a gag I just thought of.

10:57.031 --> 11:00.827
Try using it on your sweetheart
if you have one!

11:03.163 --> 11:04.456
Be ready for something.

11:06.333 --> 11:11.796
[grunting]

11:11.838 --> 11:13.089
"Don't marry me!

11:13.131 --> 11:16.343
I don't want you as my Wi-Fi!"

11:21.556 --> 11:23.099
[wind whistling]

11:23.975 --> 11:26.685
What a shitty audience!

11:26.727 --> 11:28.271
They were always jerks like you!

11:28.313 --> 11:30.106
People who forget
to laugh in the womb.

11:30.148 --> 11:32.317
And yet they always
manage to sit at the table

11:32.359 --> 11:34.528
or seat right in front
of the stage!

11:34.569 --> 11:36.154
[MEGUMI] Ever think
you're the problem?

11:36.655 --> 11:37.905
What if I am?

11:37.947 --> 11:39.282
[MEGUMI]
He has the exact same vibes.

11:39.324 --> 11:41.159
[TAKABA] Even so,
I'd never abandon you!

11:42.285 --> 11:44.454
That is because I am...

11:45.038 --> 11:48.249
an entertainer!

11:48.291 --> 11:49.376
[groans]

11:54.548 --> 11:57.592
[REGGIE] He's fast.
His curse energy skyrocketed.

11:57.634 --> 11:59.427
The shift in output is massive.

11:59.469 --> 12:02.721
- This guy is strong.
- [TAKABA] Be careful!

12:03.139 --> 12:05.183
I'm an old-school entertainer
who just recently

12:05.225 --> 12:08.186
took a strong liking
to extreme violence.

12:09.062 --> 12:11.648
Now, do you want my help,
young boy?

12:12.773 --> 12:13.900
[grunts]

12:16.695 --> 12:18.530
Let's you and I take
one of those guys each.

12:18.572 --> 12:20.781
- Hmm! Hmm, hmm, hmm!
- The younger guy, look.

12:20.823 --> 12:22.909
He can turn his body parts
into bombs.

12:23.451 --> 12:25.203
And he's using
reverse curse technique.

12:25.245 --> 12:26.287
Hmm, hmm, hmm, hmm, hmm!

12:26.329 --> 12:27.706
- Dude!
- Hmm, hmm!

12:27.746 --> 12:29.416
- Kogane!
- Yes?

12:30.291 --> 12:32.335
Hiromi Higuruma's info, now!

12:33.127 --> 12:35.129
Itadori's the one
who added that rule.

12:37.215 --> 12:39.509
I've decided that I'm done
with this colony.

12:40.594 --> 12:42.470
Back down, and I'll let you go.

12:44.097 --> 12:45.306
Huh?

12:45.348 --> 12:47.225
Where do you think
you stand in this game?

12:47.267 --> 12:48.727
I'm still owed points.

12:48.767 --> 12:51.187
The ones I lost when you
killed Hari before I could.

12:51.563 --> 12:53.481
- Hey, guy.
- The name's Takaba.

12:53.523 --> 12:54.815
Mm.

12:55.066 --> 12:57.776
If you try to kill
that bomb bastard,

12:57.818 --> 12:59.028
if you can,

12:59.529 --> 13:01.656
steal his points before you do.

13:03.241 --> 13:04.659
Okay then, young boy.

13:05.285 --> 13:06.411
I'll join you.

13:06.453 --> 13:07.828
Let's fight with honor.

13:07.870 --> 13:09.581
[epic duel music playing]

13:12.875 --> 13:15.044
But I am an entertainer.

13:15.670 --> 13:18.465
Whatever I do
has got to entertain.

13:18.839 --> 13:21.008
As long as you win,
I really don't care.

13:21.676 --> 13:22.719
[chuckles]

13:26.556 --> 13:29.100
[grunts]

13:29.392 --> 13:30.769
Sparking!

13:36.441 --> 13:38.067
What a dangerous technique!

13:38.401 --> 13:40.278
Bam! Home run!

13:40.861 --> 13:41.946
Don't worry!

13:42.322 --> 13:44.699
When it comes
to variety shows...

13:45.992 --> 13:49.245
[groaning]

13:49.287 --> 13:50.580
Where'd he...

13:52.666 --> 13:54.626
Red is prohibited.

13:54.668 --> 13:55.960
[groans]

13:58.338 --> 14:00.006
[whimpering]

14:00.047 --> 14:01.299
Not funny!

14:07.555 --> 14:09.599
I'm glad you aren't
my enemy, Takaba.

14:09.641 --> 14:13.102
[Takaba chuckles] Now, there's
a line I always wanted to hear!

14:14.937 --> 14:16.189
Later, young boy!

14:16.230 --> 14:17.357
Try not to die.

14:18.775 --> 14:20.151
Aww.

14:20.443 --> 14:22.362
Now that guy's dead too.

14:22.403 --> 14:23.613
After that humiliation,

14:23.655 --> 14:25.782
Hazenoki's about
to crush your friend.

14:26.032 --> 14:27.992
I think you should
worry about yourself.

14:28.034 --> 14:29.076
I warned you.

14:29.494 --> 14:32.246
Like I said, I've achieved
my objective in this colony.

14:32.539 --> 14:33.872
So no more holding back.

14:33.914 --> 14:35.500
I can fight for real now.

14:35.542 --> 14:36.793
Hmm.

14:39.003 --> 14:40.338
[Nue screeches]

14:44.091 --> 14:45.968
[Reggie panting]

14:51.265 --> 14:53.434
[panting]

14:58.939 --> 15:00.149
[grunts]

15:16.457 --> 15:17.834
[MEGUMI] Max Elephant!

15:18.626 --> 15:20.545
[elephant trumpets]

15:24.173 --> 15:26.593
Wow, didn't know
they came that big!

15:35.268 --> 15:36.853
[chuckles]

15:38.646 --> 15:41.982
Woo-hoo! Yeah!

15:49.031 --> 15:50.074
[grunts]

16:07.383 --> 16:08.551
[grunts]

16:08.593 --> 16:10.511
[laughs]

16:15.015 --> 16:16.058
[gasps]

16:17.268 --> 16:18.770
[chuckles]

16:34.828 --> 16:36.788
[chuckles]

16:51.636 --> 16:54.889
[REGGIE] You've figured out
my technique, haven't you?

16:54.931 --> 16:58.184
But a water attack is pretty
simplistic, don't you agree?

17:03.397 --> 17:05.817
You manifest whatever's
on those receipts.

17:06.192 --> 17:08.277
But there's more to it
than that, right?

17:08.695 --> 17:10.780
[REGGIE]
You're absolutely correct.

17:10.822 --> 17:12.490
It's hard to describe,

17:12.532 --> 17:15.743
but I'd call it
reenacting contracts.

17:15.785 --> 17:19.037
For example, I can do this, too.

17:19.079 --> 17:21.415
Contractual Re-Creation.

17:24.878 --> 17:26.629
What just burned in my hand

17:27.171 --> 17:29.507
was a receipt for a three-day,
two-night stay

17:29.549 --> 17:32.927
at the five-star
traditional inn, Hoshizoratei.

17:34.470 --> 17:36.597
In other words, my body

17:36.639 --> 17:38.307
is now as refreshed
as it would be

17:38.349 --> 17:40.100
after a restful
and relaxing vacation

17:40.142 --> 17:42.812
in a hot springs resort
for three days, two nights,

17:42.854 --> 17:44.104
plus massage.

17:44.146 --> 17:46.566
I wonder how you're faring
in comparison?

17:46.607 --> 17:48.818
No doubt you have
injuries from earlier.

17:48.860 --> 17:51.237
And you've employed
multiple shikigami.

17:51.278 --> 17:53.155
Why, you must be exhausted.

17:53.865 --> 17:56.492
[MEGUMI] I often employ
multiple shikigami at once.

17:56.993 --> 18:00.038
The problem is that
one of those was Max Elephant,

18:00.078 --> 18:01.873
which I usually use alone.

18:02.623 --> 18:05.292
[REGGIE] You can rapidly
shuffle through shikigami.

18:05.334 --> 18:07.962
But not once
they're injured, right?

18:08.004 --> 18:09.923
That's why
you can't use your dog

18:09.964 --> 18:12.090
to run, attack, and defend.

18:12.717 --> 18:14.301
And because of that,

18:14.343 --> 18:16.554
you've been forced
to use multiple

18:16.596 --> 18:19.057
one-trick shikigami all at once.

18:19.097 --> 18:20.516
It's a battle of attrition

18:20.558 --> 18:23.978
where neither of us can use
big, high-output moves.

18:24.020 --> 18:25.813
Don't you see it's futile?

18:25.855 --> 18:27.899
There's no way you can kill me.

18:29.692 --> 18:30.985
That's true.

18:31.027 --> 18:32.445
So, I'll run.

18:33.279 --> 18:34.321
Wait.

18:34.989 --> 18:36.240
[Nue screeches]

18:42.956 --> 18:44.624
[REGGIE]
It won't be that easy.

18:47.251 --> 18:48.711
[scooter whirring]

18:51.255 --> 18:53.382
[humming]

18:56.343 --> 18:58.220
A community gymnasium?

18:58.262 --> 18:59.722
Did he flee inside?

18:59.764 --> 19:01.181
Or is he luring me in?

19:01.223 --> 19:03.392
I could smoke him out
with fire,

19:03.434 --> 19:06.186
but getting into another chase
would be annoying.

19:06.228 --> 19:09.065
Well, whatever shall I do?

19:11.233 --> 19:12.401
[MEGUMI] Good.

19:12.443 --> 19:14.278
It's just as I imagined.

19:14.320 --> 19:15.947
This is the perfect size.

19:17.031 --> 19:19.617
I wonder what you have
planned for me in here,

19:19.659 --> 19:21.828
you damned little punk.

19:22.912 --> 19:25.999
You have something planned
yourself, don't you?

19:30.461 --> 19:33.589
All sorcerers tend
to tell lies now and then.

19:37.217 --> 19:39.386
[panting]

19:39.428 --> 19:40.513
[grunts]

19:46.019 --> 19:47.227
- [thuds]
- [groans]

19:48.896 --> 19:50.397
[grunts]

19:51.440 --> 19:52.650
[winces]

19:53.651 --> 19:55.111
[sword clangs]

20:02.535 --> 20:03.577
[gasps]

20:10.543 --> 20:12.128
[panting]

20:12.170 --> 20:13.546
[grunts]

20:15.673 --> 20:17.091
[whooshing]

20:17.133 --> 20:18.843
[gasps, groans]

20:25.892 --> 20:27.060
[pants]

20:27.476 --> 20:28.853
[grunts]

20:29.645 --> 20:31.814
[REGGIE] The things
I recreate from receipts

20:31.856 --> 20:33.273
are like shikigami.

20:33.315 --> 20:36.527
So I can give them simple
commands to get what I want.

20:36.569 --> 20:39.613
Knives normally don't fly,
but that one sure did.

20:40.406 --> 20:43.325
Given your personality,
I think you're going to say no.

20:43.367 --> 20:44.869
But if you transfer
your points to me,

20:44.911 --> 20:47.705
I promise I will give you
a quick and easy death

20:48.706 --> 20:51.417
[MEGUMI] Barrier techniques
are difficult, aren't they?

20:53.251 --> 20:55.171
No matter how long I've tried,

20:55.213 --> 20:57.215
I haven't been able
to get the hang of placing

20:57.255 --> 21:00.426
an artificial space
of different size over reality.

21:00.467 --> 21:01.677
Which is why...

21:02.595 --> 21:04.055
[REGGIE] No way.

21:05.598 --> 21:08.226
[MEGUMI] I'm going
to use this gymnasium as is

21:08.684 --> 21:10.603
to deploy my domain.

21:11.645 --> 21:13.439
[REGGIE] He can do that?

21:33.333 --> 21:35.502
[MEGUMI] Domain Expansion.

21:36.254 --> 21:38.631
Chimera Shadow Garden.

21:38.672 --> 21:40.591
[thudding, beeping]

21:44.762 --> 21:47.640
[REGGIE] I didn't know he was
a sorcerer on that level.

21:48.182 --> 21:49.934
[MEGUMI] I never said

21:49.976 --> 21:52.394
I didn't have any big moves.

21:55.273 --> 21:57.441
[♪ closing theme song playing]

23:25.821 --> 23:28.574
[MEGUMI] Even incomplete,
a domain is still a domain!

23:28.615 --> 23:31.035
[REGGIE] I'm pulling out
my trump card and activating it!

23:31.077 --> 23:32.661
[MEGUMI] Not yet!
Endure a little longer!

23:32.703 --> 23:34.080
[REGGIE]
I acknowledge your strength.

23:34.121 --> 23:35.831
[MEGUMI] Which of us
will get crushed first?

23:35.873 --> 23:38.251
[REGGIE] Get crushed!
